346
00:25:35,484 --> 00:25:37,405
SUN-WOO FROM MARAIS

347
00:25:49,427 --> 00:25:50,733
Hey, Sun-woo.

348
00:25:51,905 --> 00:25:53,561
It's me. Long time no talk.

349
00:25:53,644 --> 00:25:54,615
Hey, Yu-mi.

350
00:25:55,532 --> 00:25:57,088
Are you well?

351
00:25:57,171 --> 00:25:59,663
No, I'm not doing well.

352
00:25:59,746 --> 00:26:01,486
I think
Marais will go out of business soon.

353
00:26:02,209 --> 00:26:03,767
Why?

354
00:26:03,850 --> 00:26:06,179
You don't know yet, do you?

355
00:26:06,831 --> 00:26:11,089
Mr. Lee passed away last year
due to a stroke.

356
00:26:11,172 --> 00:26:12,223
I see.

357
00:26:12,740 --> 00:26:16,163
Little Director came back to Korea
last month to get a divorce.

358
00:26:17,155 --> 00:26:19,956
But she owes her husband money
because of stocks.

359
00:26:20,882 --> 00:26:24,055
The family already sold
two buildings last year.

360
00:26:24,138 --> 00:26:28,816
You know, Little Director
never had a worry in her life before.

361
00:26:28,899 --> 00:26:31,755
These days, she's scarier than Mr. Lee
whenever someone mentions money.

362
00:26:31,838 --> 00:26:33,291
She just screams her head off.

363
00:26:34,536 --> 00:26:36,826
Ms. Kim was the first to quit.

364
00:26:37,959 --> 00:26:39,410
Is she planning to stay here?

365
00:26:40,527 --> 00:26:44,367
She said she'll go back, but I'm not sure.

366
00:26:44,450 --> 00:26:47,421
I heard she started
a fashion business there with a celebrity.

367
00:26:52,843 --> 00:26:53,788
Professor Lee.

368
00:26:54,467 --> 00:26:56,294
It's past 7:00 p.m.
Aren't you going home?

369
00:26:57,417 --> 00:26:59,726
You must have a lot on your mind.

370
00:26:59,809 --> 00:27:01,356
I'll head out first.

371
00:27:02,593 --> 00:27:03,525
Okay.

372
00:27:12,681 --> 00:27:14,108
Wow, it smells good.

373
00:27:16,251 --> 00:27:17,709
Why did you come unannounced?

374
00:27:17,792 --> 00:27:20,403
I could've ordered some in advance
if you did.

375
00:27:21,561 --> 00:27:25,364
I suddenly remembered
that you have Wednesdays off.

376
00:27:26,266 --> 00:27:27,640
This is delicious.

377
00:27:27,723 --> 00:27:29,926
It's even better
since I didn't expect to eat this.

378
00:27:33,060 --> 00:27:34,224
Ji-won.

379
00:27:34,307 --> 00:27:35,294
Yes?

380
00:27:36,396 --> 00:27:40,975
Why do you want to become
a political journalist?

381
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:46,974
I'm not sure. Well...

382
00:27:47,057 --> 00:27:51,180
I kind of feel a sense of duty.

383
00:27:52,657 --> 00:27:56,328
These people always talk about
beliefs and justice,

384
00:27:57,975 --> 00:28:00,661
but in actuality, they get together

385
00:28:00,744 --> 00:28:04,438
to rig everything and lie.

386
00:28:04,521 --> 00:28:07,670
And when these people get caught,

387
00:28:07,753 --> 00:28:09,124
they're never sorry.

388
00:28:12,945 --> 00:28:15,516
Someone needs to teach them a lesson.
Don't you agree?

389
00:28:20,186 --> 00:28:24,653
They promised to make me
a political correspondent after China,

390
00:28:24,736 --> 00:28:25,667
but they keep delaying it.

391
00:28:25,750 --> 00:28:28,939
I knew it.
It's exactly like what happens in movies.

392
00:28:30,391 --> 00:28:31,287
What?

393
00:28:32,596 --> 00:28:35,107
"After this job,
you'll be free to leave the gang."

394
00:28:35,190 --> 00:28:36,895
"This is the last job."

395
00:28:36,978 --> 00:28:37,933
You know what I mean, right?

396
00:28:39,658 --> 00:28:43,096
But no one ever keeps their promise
in these movies.

397
00:28:44,261 --> 00:28:45,736
Yet I fell for it too.

398
00:28:56,582 --> 00:28:58,979
Yu-mi, did something happen?

399
00:28:59,062 --> 00:29:00,484
You're not yourself today.

400
00:29:03,895 --> 00:29:04,943
No, I'm okay.

401
00:29:05,845 --> 00:29:09,832
I'm just tired.

402
00:29:11,757 --> 00:29:13,839
What? What is it?

403
00:29:18,991 --> 00:29:20,441
Ji-won, do you know this?

404
00:29:22,861 --> 00:29:27,400
They say autumn is the season for reading,

405
00:29:29,118 --> 00:29:32,121
but it started as a marketing strategy
because it used to be a low sales season.

406
00:29:33,181 --> 00:29:34,552
Seriously?

407
00:29:35,910 --> 00:29:37,218
I see.

408
00:29:38,015 --> 00:29:40,680
They say you'll live well
if you move on a rainy day

409
00:29:41,934 --> 00:29:46,035
because it's really tiring to move
when it rains.

410
00:29:47,192 --> 00:29:48,997
They made up the saying to encourage you.

411
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:54,403
Sayings like "No pain, no gain" too.

412
00:29:55,793 --> 00:29:57,506
When people realize
these sayings are fake,

413
00:29:59,016 --> 00:30:01,273
they won't live to their fullest.

414
00:30:15,119 --> 00:30:16,170
Don't pick up.

415
00:30:18,399 --> 00:30:19,273
Why not?

416
00:30:19,356 --> 00:30:21,253
It's probably someone
complaining about the noise.

417
00:30:23,340 --> 00:30:25,503
It's late. Do it later.

418
00:30:49,929 --> 00:30:53,205
It only takes 2 or 3 minutes.
Why are people so impatient?

419
00:31:00,164 --> 00:31:01,702
Geez.

420
00:31:08,830 --> 00:31:10,224
Can we move?

421
00:31:17,226 --> 00:31:18,380
Why all of a sudden?

422
00:31:25,499 --> 00:31:29,918
I want to live where I can
open the windows all the way.

423
00:31:30,723 --> 00:31:32,742
All high-rises are like this.

424
00:31:41,660 --> 00:31:42,789
It's suffocating.

425
00:31:44,274 --> 00:31:47,518
But everyone's jealous of our place
even when the windows don't open.

426
00:31:48,259 --> 00:31:51,010
We're like a symbol that tells them,

427
00:31:51,093 --> 00:31:53,185
they can become like us if they work hard.

428
00:31:56,668 --> 00:32:00,143
People will say it's too extravagant
during the election campaign.

429
00:32:01,621 --> 00:32:03,527
I said, I bought this place
so people would talk about it.

430
00:32:17,763 --> 00:32:19,935
I met with Ji-won.

431
00:32:20,018 --> 00:32:21,012
Okay.

432
00:32:23,224 --> 00:32:26,708
Korea Daily?
That company doesn't seem so good.

433
00:32:27,465 --> 00:32:28,300
I see.

434
00:32:28,383 --> 00:32:31,390
Is there a position you can make for her?

435
00:32:31,473 --> 00:32:32,644
At a political desk.

436
00:32:37,586 --> 00:32:38,955
That would be no problem at all.

437
00:32:41,433 --> 00:32:43,819
People won't talk bad about you
even if you get her a position.

438
00:32:43,902 --> 00:32:47,401
She's smart and is a person of principles.

439
00:32:51,197 --> 00:32:52,288
Okay.

440
00:32:55,213 --> 00:32:56,671
But I have a condition.

441
00:32:58,237 --> 00:33:01,496
You should try to get along
with the wives of the assemblymen.

442
00:33:07,093 --> 00:33:08,833
I can't get along with them.

443
00:33:11,022 --> 00:33:12,393
Just humor them.

444
00:33:13,125 --> 00:33:16,289
You should be at the center
of all social gatherings.

445
00:33:17,157 --> 00:33:19,640
The real information will come out
from the mouths of those women.

446
00:33:20,861 --> 00:33:23,528
Fine. But please smoke outside.

447
00:33:34,385 --> 00:33:37,130
Is Bokuk Daily's Director Kim in Korea?

448
00:33:54,416 --> 00:33:55,712
Hello?

449
00:33:55,795 --> 00:33:58,648
Are you Korea Daily's Han Ji-won?

450
00:33:58,731 --> 00:34:00,097
Yes, this is she.

451
00:34:00,732 --> 00:34:03,906
I'm calling from Bokuk Daily's HR team.

452
00:34:03,989 --> 00:34:05,655
Okay. And?

453
00:34:05,738 --> 00:34:07,824
If you're free,

454
00:34:07,907 --> 00:34:11,473
I can go near Korea Daily's office
in about two hours.

455
00:34:11,556 --> 00:34:12,895
Shall we meet for a moment?

456
00:34:14,339 --> 00:34:16,862
I can, but what is this about?

457
00:34:17,468 --> 00:34:20,223
To offer you a position.

458
00:34:20,306 --> 00:34:21,293
Pardon?

459
00:34:21,945 --> 00:34:24,791
Okay, Assemblyman Min.

460
00:34:24,874 --> 00:34:26,997
What is it that you want to do now?

461
00:34:30,316 --> 00:34:32,457
You should take responsibility
for what you said.

462
00:34:32,540 --> 00:34:34,833
You can't take your word back now.

463
00:34:38,174 --> 00:34:41,807
So a verbal promise isn't a promise?

464
00:34:48,180 --> 00:34:50,929
Twenty-third floor. The door's opening.

465
00:34:51,012 --> 00:34:52,894
She was trying to fix it by herself...

466
00:34:54,451 --> 00:34:58,255
Hyun-joo might seem old enough...

467
00:34:58,338 --> 00:34:59,452
Yes.

468
00:34:59,535 --> 00:35:02,369
But she knows nothing about the world.

469
00:35:02,824 --> 00:35:04,315
The door's closing.

470
00:35:04,398 --> 00:35:05,671
Exactly.

471
00:35:06,844 --> 00:35:09,434
Do you know how much debt
that hospital has?

472
00:35:09,517 --> 00:35:11,230
It's crazy.

473
00:35:11,313 --> 00:35:12,485
Yes.

474
00:35:14,242 --> 00:35:16,166
If he took care of things well,

475
00:35:16,249 --> 00:35:18,277
she wouldn't have invested in stocks.

476
00:35:21,018 --> 00:35:22,913
Basement level one.

477
00:35:22,996 --> 00:35:24,645
The door's opening.

478
00:35:25,506 --> 00:35:29,181
We'll just give them the money as soon as
the building sells to finish it off.

479
00:35:30,420 --> 00:35:33,352
It'll really ruin her at this rate.

480
00:35:33,435 --> 00:35:34,694
Yes. Right now?

481
00:35:34,777 --> 00:35:37,904
I came to feed Hyun-joo's dog,
and now I'm on my way to the lawyer.

482
00:35:38,563 --> 00:35:39,763
All I have is my daughter.

483
00:35:39,846 --> 00:35:42,408
There's nothing I can't do for her.

484
00:36:08,093 --> 00:36:09,506
What's your job?

485
00:36:10,365 --> 00:36:11,524
I'm sorry, Sir.

486
00:36:12,722 --> 00:36:16,278
I messaged you to ask you
to come down after ten minutes.

487
00:36:16,361 --> 00:36:17,589
I guess you didn't see it.

488
00:36:18,217 --> 00:36:19,308
You messaged me?

489
00:36:22,513 --> 00:36:23,995
Did you say you messaged me?

490
00:36:25,521 --> 00:36:27,213
I left home early,

491
00:36:27,296 --> 00:36:29,717
but there was an accident
on Inner Ring Expressway.

492
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:32,917
The exits are few and far between there.

493
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:34,038
I'm so sorry.

494
00:36:34,681 --> 00:36:36,162
It's basic to be on time.

495
00:36:36,245 --> 00:36:37,719
Also, look at the car.

496
00:36:39,611 --> 00:36:41,480
I got a car wash yesterday,

497
00:36:41,563 --> 00:36:43,849
but it rained overnight.

498
00:36:44,506 --> 00:36:47,433
I couldn't look after it today.

499
00:36:47,516 --> 00:36:48,615
I'm so sorry.

500
00:36:49,389 --> 00:36:52,211
You never tried preparing in advance,
have you?

501
00:36:52,294 --> 00:36:53,716
Today was an exception.

502
00:36:53,799 --> 00:36:55,170
I'll get things right next time, sir.

503
00:36:55,253 --> 00:36:56,951
Why always next time?

504
00:37:04,134 --> 00:37:07,226
Do you know what's common
among people like you?

505
00:37:09,910 --> 00:37:11,058
You're lazy,

506
00:37:12,501 --> 00:37:13,656
impatient,

507
00:37:15,910 --> 00:37:17,289
and full of excuses.

508
00:37:23,374 --> 00:37:24,426
Honey!

509
00:37:24,509 --> 00:37:27,611
Mr. Kim, wake up.

510
00:37:28,814 --> 00:37:31,603
How will you make a living like this?

511
00:37:31,686 --> 00:37:34,737
You can't survive in this harsh world
like this.

512
00:37:36,239 --> 00:37:37,705
Please stop.

513
00:37:37,788 --> 00:37:38,846
Stop!

514
00:37:41,796 --> 00:37:43,450
Step aside.

515
00:37:43,533 --> 00:37:45,744
Go over there and stay out.

516
00:37:46,401 --> 00:37:47,377
Keep your mouth shut.

517
00:38:02,959 --> 00:38:04,162
Do you feel wronged?

518
00:38:05,084 --> 00:38:06,780
After all,

519
00:38:08,364 --> 00:38:10,462
you did send a text.

520
00:38:12,451 --> 00:38:16,069
You did your best. You did all you could.

521
00:38:17,915 --> 00:38:19,317
What could be the problem?

522
00:38:22,539 --> 00:38:23,594
Geez.

523
00:38:28,725 --> 00:38:29,721
Hey.

524
00:38:33,283 --> 00:38:34,825
I'm sorry, Sir.

525
00:38:34,908 --> 00:38:37,225
This won't ever happen again.

526
00:38:37,308 --> 00:38:38,778
It was nice having you.

527
00:38:43,028 --> 00:38:45,470
- What a morning.
- Sir.

528
00:38:46,196 --> 00:38:49,137
Sir, I'll fix my mistake.

529
00:38:49,220 --> 00:38:50,176
Sir.

530
00:38:51,148 --> 00:38:52,135
Sir.

531
00:39:04,437 --> 00:39:06,296
KOREA DAILY

532
00:39:11,634 --> 00:39:12,892
Aren't you going to eat?

533
00:39:13,516 --> 00:39:15,260
No. I'll eat later.

534
00:39:17,057 --> 00:39:18,622
Enjoy your lunch.

535
00:39:25,284 --> 00:39:26,494
Living expenses...

536
00:39:27,416 --> 00:39:29,044
When did it ever go down?

537
00:39:32,761 --> 00:39:34,443
Sure.

538
00:39:34,526 --> 00:39:37,404
This is a huge exclusive

539
00:39:37,487 --> 00:39:41,015
only Han Ji-won can write about.

540
00:39:41,766 --> 00:39:43,656
BOKUK DAILY, LEE YOON-GEOL

541
00:39:44,394 --> 00:39:45,614
Sir!

542
00:39:46,546 --> 00:39:49,581
If Bokuk Daily is scouting me,
should I go or not?

543
00:39:51,010 --> 00:39:53,421
Are you stupid? Of course, you should.

544
00:39:58,089 --> 00:39:59,093
Ta-da.

545
00:40:00,137 --> 00:40:02,198
What is this?

546
00:40:05,411 --> 00:40:09,076
You mentioned you used to like
the Crazy Donut in front of our school.

547
00:40:11,474 --> 00:40:12,508
Right.

548
00:40:14,170 --> 00:40:15,151
Did I say that?

549
00:40:15,858 --> 00:40:17,128
I was reminded of you,

550
00:40:17,211 --> 00:40:19,668
so I went there in a hurry
just before going to the airport.

551
00:40:19,751 --> 00:40:20,988
Are you proud of me?

552
00:40:23,502 --> 00:40:25,446
Yes. Thank you.

553
00:40:25,529 --> 00:40:26,938
It didn't even cross my mind.

554
00:40:27,527 --> 00:40:31,428
Ms. Lee, I heard you're a professor now.

555
00:40:31,864 --> 00:40:33,308
Congratulations.

556
00:40:34,764 --> 00:40:38,607
You know how Professor Joseph
always says the same thing in class?

557
00:40:40,802 --> 00:40:42,263
The Law of Jante.

558
00:40:42,346 --> 00:40:44,897
The sentiment
is completely different from Korea.

559
00:40:44,980 --> 00:40:47,041
Thanks to him,

560
00:40:47,124 --> 00:40:49,713
I want to go to a graduate school
in northern Europe.

561
00:40:50,324 --> 00:40:54,800
It's so unfamiliar to me and exotic...

562
00:42:07,231 --> 00:42:09,541
...criticized Francoist dictatorship

563
00:42:09,624 --> 00:42:11,622
and showed Leftist tendencies...

564
00:42:24,337 --> 00:42:26,163
One, two, three.

565
00:42:43,853 --> 00:42:46,206
JOINT SPEECH SESSION
FOR SEOUL METROPOLITAN AREA

566
00:43:02,730 --> 00:43:04,747
He said he drew just as well

567
00:43:04,830 --> 00:43:07,472
as Raphael when he was 12.

568
00:44:10,388 --> 00:44:11,480
Lee Yu-mi.

569
00:44:15,331 --> 00:44:17,253
I think you owe me an explanation.

570
00:44:27,270 --> 00:44:29,627
UNIT 2302
TO LEE ANNA

